SIMPLE: resurrect
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resurrect
<hw>Res`ur*rect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Resurrection</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take from the grave;
to disinter.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To reanimate; to restore to life; to bring to view
(that which was forgotten or lost).</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resurrection</ent>⟦br⟧
